rComments: Easy A+ and his classes can be interesting. Doesn't waste time teaching us a bunch of stuff we will just forget anyway. Doesn't take the program seriously, which is fine, since we are basically just there for our Placement experience. Recommended.

Great teacher, great class! We have a lot of fun, and do a lot of activities, but he makes sure to do a debrief after to discuss some of the things (learning) that went on.  Some people think that his class is a joke, but if you take the time to really think about the class, you realize just how much effort and preparation he puts into his lessons.

we did lots of great drama activities, he is fun and engaging.  you will enjoy this class.  be prepared to enjoy a nite of Evening Star.  but do buy some good art and music books cause you wont do much in his class
Although he didn't cover the entire curriculum, what he did cover, he covered quite well.  His warm friendly personality and novel teaching style guaranteed that I always look forward to his class.
Great prof. We had a lot of fun during his classes. Great, just great person and professeur!
The only prof at UO that gave me any preparation for teaching! He's the only one you need...and he has the BEST stories...

He always had great examples.  I felt he went too easy on the students who did not want to participate however (told them they didnt' have to show up to class).  I put in effort, yet got the same marks.  Too easy.  But fun class.
Amazingly caring and sensitive. Really listens to the students in his reflective seminar and does what he can to help us through any difficulties.
I'm so lucky to be in his Reflective Seminar! He does what he can to relieve the stress...what a GREAT guy! And don't forget about the EVENING STAR!
He would have been hot, in his day...An absolutely wonderful person, years after you graduate, you'll be going back to visit Michael.
